'''Single Radio Voice Call Continuity''' ('''SRVCC''') provides an interim solution for handing over [[VoLTE]] (Voice over LTE) to 2G/3G networks. The voice calls on LTE network are meant to be packet switched calls which use [[IP Multimedia Subsystem|IMS]] system to be made. To make it inter operable with existing networks, these calls are to be handed over to Circuit switched calls in GSM/WCDMA networks. QoS is ensured by SRVCC operators for calls made.

3GPP also standardized SRVCC to provide easy handovers from LTE network to GSM/UMTS network.

